<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-RANGERS-SATHER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SATHER NEARS RANGERS PACT 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; NEW YORK _ Although Glen Sather insists that he is biding his
time, it is apparent that he and the Rangers are in the final
stages of a deal that would make him the New York Rangers' new
president and general manager.
</P>
<P>
   Several NHL officials confirmed Friday that the only issue
remaining in the talks was compensation.
</P>
<P>
   One league official said the Rangers are offering Sather $11
million over five years. Sather is asking for $15 million over five
years, the official said.
</P>
<P>
   Stock options in Cablevision, which owns the Rangers, the Knicks
and Madison Square Garden, are also believed to be part of any deal
made.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not in a hurry to do anything,'' Sather said Friday.
``There's no deal.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
