   ''Basically he got mad at me for tracking the ball through the
zone. I do that all the time. I want to see if the ball goes over
the plate.''
</P>
<P>
   ''He did say something,'' said crew chief Ed Montague. ''He
leaned out over the plate looking at the pitch. That can be an
attempt to show up the umpire.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I said don't be doing that and he did it again,'' Randazzo
said of Anderson tracking the pitch. ''He said 'What are you going
to do about it?' and I ejected him.''
</P>
<P>
   Randazzo first reached the majors last year in the National
League for the last month of the season. Montague had been in the
National League for 25 years before this season, when the umpires
work in both leagues.
</P>
<P>
   ''You know what the problem is?'' Montague said. ''(Randazzo)
doesn't know the kid, he doesn't know his body language. You learn
body language. Whenever a kid reacts like that it puts an umpire in
a corner.''
</P>
<P>
   Scioscia said he felt Randazzo was the aggressor and was wrong
in throwing out his center fielder.
</P>
<P>
   ''I thought Tony was really out of line,'' Scioscia said. ''The
umpire was far too aggressive in that situation. Garret didn't say
anything. He shows up and plays the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Before all the fireworks late in the game, Etherton settled into
a groove in the middle innings.
</P>
<P>
   ''Things went pretty well until the sixth,'' said Etherton, who
gave up three runs and seven hits. ''I was able to settle down a
little bit and make pitches when I needed to. My biggest struggle
tonight was my inconsistent delivery. I was flying open a little
bit. It had to do with an adrenaline rush. I've never had that many
people watch me pitch.''
</P>
<P>
   In the crowd was Etherton's family, which came out from Orange
County for the game.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels took a 2-1 lead in the second inning on Anderson's
two- run homer (No. 12). Bengie Molina's two-out, RBI single in the
fourth made it 3-1 and Darin Erstad's solo homer (No. 7) in the
fifth gave the Angels a 4-1 lead.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
