being a Catholic who is unapologetically pro-choice on abortion,
yet he remains prominently featured on Gov. George W. Bush's list
of potential running mates. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   With a photo.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-WESTPOINT (West Point, N.Y.) _ Vice President Al Gore gives
the commencement address at the U.S. Military Academy. By Katharine
Q. Seelye. Eds: Could move late afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   NY-SENATE-RACE (Undated) _ The New York Senate race has been
transformed from a battle over a tiny number of undecided voters
into a broad and complex contest, with voting blocs and geographic
preferences that had seemed fixed suddenly up for grabs after Mayor
Rudolph Giuliani's departure, Republican and Democratic strategists
say. By Eric Nagourney.
</P>
