was all someone else's problem until Michael Bradford, U.S.
attorney in Beaumont, Texas, agreed to step in last year after the
case was removed from the local U.S. attorney's office. Story
primarily focused on him and his role in this pivotal case for the
government. By Tommy Witherspoon. (Witherspoon, Waco
Tribune-Herald). 50. FILE ART AVAILABLE.
