happy. But the only way the teen loner knows how to deal with her
gloomy existence is by harming herself. She stabs herself with
tools. Slices her wrists with glass. Burns her arm with a cigarette
lighter. Her body looks like a grotesque human pin cushion. Dawn
may not control her life, but, she reasons, she can be in charge of
