<P>
   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-HUNTING _ ATLANTA _ ``Gobble,'' he said. Silence. Far
away, a crow cawed. ``Gobblegobblegobble,'' he continued,
passionately, flogging a fallen tree trunk with his hat to make a
sound like the beating of large wings. Still no reply. Finally Doug
Benefield got to his feet, shaking his head in disgust. ``He's a
wise old bird,'' Benefield said. ``He's gone.'' Benefield is a
master of the art of talking to turkeys, but this time he was
unable to persuade an old tom to venture across the sights of his
shotgun. It tended to prove that the suburban South Fulton County
turkey is just as wily as his country cousin. (Warner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS and LAYOUT.
</P>
